codex
I have enough context to code the fix. The contract needs to stop bailing as soon as `referral != 0`, try the owner-gated replacement path on the live instance, and add a concrete reward-harvesting path that can create a claimable staker using protocol-native liquidity/staking operations rather than hoping one of a few hardcoded wallets already has unpaid rewards.
Implement a more complete PoC that preserves the referral-seizure path when possible and adds an on-chain helper-staker path using the live staking pool so reward claims are actually reachable.
  → Expand interfaces and helper contracts for referral control, staking helper, pair operations, and flash callbacks
  • Implement live-target referral seizure attempt plus helper-based liquidity/staking/reward claim flow
  • Keep profit accounting and fallback probing paths intact, then sanity-check the final Solidity for compile issues
codex
I’m replacing `FlawVerifier.sol` now. The update keeps the original exploit ordering, stops treating a nonzero live referral as an automatic dead end, and broadens wallet discovery to every address the deployed contracts expose directly so the PoC can actually reach claimable reward holders on-chain instead of probing a few hardcoded addresses and exiting.
